	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?item=17778&mid=104026319569656>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?item=17778&mid=104026319569656>RE: Question???</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?item=17778&mid=104026319569656#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Dec 18th 9:24 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=141170><span id= >Azeil, Eater of Souls</span></a><br><span id=notbold>61 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.26]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Ok, here is what i have heard.&nbsp;&nbsp;Before AC is taken into acount, take the damage your weapon was going to do, and add the dmg bonus.  For example, lets say a 34 dmg weapon was going to hit for 100, and the damage bonus was 14.  Then you have a possobilitie of hitting 114 damage.  Now, if the creatures AC blocks 110 of it, then it only takes 4 damage, but it increases your max POSSIBLE damage by that number<br><br>Kazadorm Blightsbane&lt;Sons of Kings&gt;</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
